  "id": "019d32df-f594-74a0-a4e6-dec6fa89248a",
  "content": "# Agent Teams Adapter RFC: Post-Review Status\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-28\n**Doc:** repos/corvia/docs/rfcs/2026-03-28-agent-teams-adapter-design.md\n**Status:** Draft, reviewed by 5 personas, fixes applied\n\n## Review Summary\n5 reviewers (Senior SWE, PM, QA, Security, Integration Architect) all said \"Ready to implement with fixes\" at High confidence. No critical blockers.\n\n## Fixes Applied (12 total)\n1. Hook security baseline: input validation, path traversal prevention, umask 077, atomic writes\n2. Concurrent write protection: flock for tasks.jsonl, atomic rename for file copies\n3. SessionEnd sweep scoped to relevant team only, wrapped in error handler\n4. Conditional hook installation (only if Agent Teams enabled)\n5. Multi-domain dispatch: source_path based routing, two corvia.toml entries\n6. Team end timestamp + status (completed/abandoned) in team structure entry\n7. content_role: \"task\" not \"plan\" for task entries\n8. assigned_to edge points to teammate session entry (not team)\n9. Added ran_during edge (team lifecycle, distinct from has_member)\n10. Deferred edge wiring via .pending-edges for adapter ordering independence\n11. Broadcast message dedup: hash(sender+content+timestamp)\n12. Expanded test plan: 8 -> 16 tests with fixtures\n\n## Ready for Implementation\nAll reviewer concerns addressed. The RFC is ready for Phase 1 (hooks) implementation.\n",
